<LETTER>
<HEAD>Another from the same.</HEAD>
<OPENER><SALUTE>Honour Mr. Governor,</SALUTE>
<DATE>May 15, 1685.</DATE></OPENER>
<P>NOW this day I com your house, I want se you, and I bring my hand at before you I want shake hand to you if your worship when please then you receve my hand then shake your hand and my hand. You my friend be|cause I remember at old time when live my grant father and grant mother then Englishmen com this country, then my grant father and Englishmen they make a good govenant, they friend allwayes, my grant father leving at place called Malamake rever, other name chef Natukkog and Panukkog, that one rever great many names, and I bring you this few skins at this first time I will give you, my friend. This all Indian hand.</P>
